{"id":60593,"title":"How we evaluate and treat neutropenia in adults.","abstract":"Isolated neutropenia is a common clinical problem seen by primary care physicians and hematologists. The evaluation of neutropenia is dictated by the acuity of the clinical presentation and the duration, age, and clinical status of the patient. In this review, we provide a practical approach to the evaluation of the adult patient with neutropenia, with the major focus on the evaluation of neutropenia in the outpatient setting. ","date":"2014-08-22","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24869938","annotations":[{"name":"Physician","weight":0.783378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician"},{"name":"Primary care","weight":0.776572,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primary_care"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.681948,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Primary care physician","weight":0.676635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primary_care_physician"},{"name":"Outpatient","weight":0.623769,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outpatient"},{"name":"Hematology","weight":0.579861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hematology"},{"name":"Neutropenia","weight":0.116968,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neutropenia"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.0471248,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaluation"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.0320572,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Adult","weight":0.0311179,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adult"},{"name":"Visual acuity","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_acuity"},{"name":"Time","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time"},{"name":"Presentation","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.o